{"lemma":"عِذارٌ","slug":"عِذارٌ","root":"ع.ذ.ر","root_slug":"ع-ذ-ر","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ذ-ر","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":3},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n28442"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%90%D8%B0%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cheek"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"fluff, first growth of beard (on the cheeks)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"cheekpiece (of a horse's harness)"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n28442","headword_ar":"عِذَارٌ","root":"E*r","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain appertenance of a horse"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O;) i. e. the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"strap,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the bridle,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, M, Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that lies,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extends down,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the cheek,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, Mgh, Msb, K,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two cheeks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T,) of the horse (T, M, Mgh, Msb, K) or the like: (T, Mgh, Msb:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ea*aAraAni","text_ar":"عَذَارَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"are the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two straps upon the two cheeks"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the horse,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the right and left:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd in his Book on the Saddle and Bridle:) or, as some say, the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aAr","text_ar":"عِذَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two straps"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the bridle"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that meet at the back of the neck:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) [thus it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"either of the two cheek-straps,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, accord. to some, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two cheek-straps together, that compose the headstall:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] some say that it is called by the name of its place; but the converse is the case accord. to others: (TA:) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aAru Alr~asani","text_ar":"عِذَارُ الرَّسَنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the appertance, of the halter, corresponding to the cheek-strap,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cheek-straps, of the bridle"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"headstall:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see a verse of Ibn-Mukbil cited voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasanN","text_ar":"رَسَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":)] pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*urN","text_ar":"عُذُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K, [in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*orN","text_ar":"عُذْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]) like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kutubN","text_ar":"كُتُبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kitaAbN","text_ar":"كِتَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb, TA.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lalofaqoru A^azoyanu lilomuw^omini","text_ar":"لَلْفَقْرُ اَزْيَنُ لِلْمُوْمِنِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mino Ei*aArK HasanK EalaY xad~i farasK","text_ar":"مِنْ عِذَارٍ حَسَنٍ عَلَى خَدِّ فَرَسٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Verily poverty is more ornamental to the believer than a beautiful cheek-strap,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"headstall, upon the cheek of a horse"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"farasN qaSiyru AlEi*aAri","text_ar":"فَرَسٌ قَصِيرُ العِذَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A horse short in the cheek-strap,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"headstall,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] implies commendation, as denoting width of the lip. (TA, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EinaAnN","text_ar":"عِنَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aArN","text_ar":"عِذَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thing that connects the leading-rope"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Habola AlxiTaAmi","text_ar":"حَبْلَ الخِطَامِ"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the head of the he-camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and of the she-camel."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A halter;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasanN","text_ar":"رَسَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEa*~arN","text_ar":"مُعَذَّرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a halter"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rasan","text_ar":"رَسَن"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a double"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aAr","text_ar":"عِذَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw Ei*aArayoni","text_ar":"ذُو عِذَارَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (TA.) One says,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN $adiydu AlEi*aAri","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ شَدِيدُ العِذَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is strong in respect of determination."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaliyEu AlEi*aAri","text_ar":"خَلِيعُ العِذَارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is weak in respect of determination;"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"is a person who has thrown off restraint;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] like a horse that has no bridle upon him, and that therefore falls upon his face. (TA. [See also art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xlE","text_ar":"خلع"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaEa Ei*aArahu","text_ar":"خَلَعَ عِذَارَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He threw off restraint;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he persisted in error:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he departed from obedience, and persisted in error:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he broke off from his family,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disagreed with them, and wearied them by his wickedness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ta$aATara","text_ar":"تَشَاطَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xlE muEa*~arahu","text_ar":"خلع مُعَذَّرَهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A:) or the latter means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he did not obey a director in the right course:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, TA:) or, in the former phrase, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aAr","text_ar":"عِذَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"shame;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xalaEa Ei*aArahu","text_ar":"خَلَعَ عِذَارَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he divested himself of shame;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like as a horse casts off his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E*Ar","text_ar":"عذار"},{"kind":"text","text":", and becomes refractory, overcoming his rider and running away with him. (TA. [See, again, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xlE","text_ar":"خلع"},{"kind":"text","text":".]) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lawaY Eanohu Ei*aArahu","text_ar":"لَوَى عَنْهُ عِذَارَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He disobeyed him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two sides of the beard:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"either side"},{"kind":"text","text":"thereof; (Mgh, TA;) the two sides thereof being called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aAraA All~iHoyapi","text_ar":"عِذَارَا اللِّحْيَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEi*aAraAni","text_ar":"العِذَارَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) because they are in the place [corresponding to that] of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E*Ar","text_ar":"عذار"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the horse or the like: (Mgh, * TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a boy,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that grows evenly in the place of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aAr","text_ar":"عِذَار"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the beard,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that descends upon the two jaws:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or a man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair that grows in the place of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aAr","text_ar":"عِذَار"},{"kind":"text","text":": (O, TA:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"line of the beard:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that is in front of the ear, and between which and the ear is a whiteness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har pp. 208-9:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of the face,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon which grows the hair in a lengthened form in front of the lobula of the ear"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extending"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to the base of the jaw."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 495.) ―         -b3-  And (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cheek;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEa*~arN","text_ar":"مُعَذَّرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) which latter [properly] signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aAr","text_ar":"عِذَار"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, TA,) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"place of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aAraAni","text_ar":"عِذَارَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O.) You say, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN Tawiylu AlmuEa*~ari","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ طَوِيلُ المُعَذَّرِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one is long in the place of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aAr","text_ar":"عِذَار"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, TA.) ―         -b4-  And (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mark made"},{"kind":"text","text":"[on a camel (see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maEo*uwrN","text_ar":"مَعْذُورٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with a hot iron in the place of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aAr","text_ar":"عِذَار"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, O, K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*orapN","text_ar":"عُذْرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"on the back of the neck, extending to the temples:"},{"kind":"text","text":"so in the Tedhkireh of Aboo-'Alee; but the former explanation is the better known: El-Ahmar mentions ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*orN","text_ar":"عُذْرٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one kind of the marks made with a hot iron."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  Also (tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two sharp sides"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"edges,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) or [rather]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"either of these,"},{"kind":"text","text":"for both together are called the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ei*aAraAni","text_ar":"عِذَارَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) of a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naSol","text_ar":"نَصْل"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. of the iron head of an arrow or of a spear &c.]. (K, TA.) ―         -b6-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Either side"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a road, (A,) and of a valley, (A, TA,) and of a wall. (TA.) ―         -b7-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A row"},{"kind":"text","text":"of trees, (TA,) or of palm-trees. (A.) ―         -b8-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An elongated tract"},{"kind":"text","text":"of sand. (A.) The dual as used in a verse of Dhu-r-Rummeh means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two elongated tracts"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HabolaAni","text_ar":"حَبْلَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in the CK"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jabalAni","text_ar":"جَبَلانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"])"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two sides thereof:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two roads"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyqaAni","text_ar":"طَرِيقَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (S, O, K, TA.) ―         -b9-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rugged tract of ground,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA,) and ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tract"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of sand,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lying across in a wide plain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu*urN","text_ar":"عُذُرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)       -A2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iEo*aArN","text_ar":"اـِعْذَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".       -A3-  It also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Resistance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"refusal;"},{"kind":"text","text":"from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AltaEa*~ur","text_ar":"التَعَذُّر"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["T","M","Mgh","Msb","K","TA","S","O","A","As"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}